--[[
    CombinedAutoActions.lua

    This LocalScript creates a draggable GUI with three independent sections:

      1. Auto Click (Tap):
         - Continuously finds the block with the HIGHEST "Number" value (read from the Text property of the
           TextLabel inside each block’s "Back" SurfaceGui) and constantly fires the "Tap" event on it.
         - It prints a notification when a new best block is identified.
      
      2. Auto Merge (TakeBlock):
         - Groups blocks by the Text property from their "Back" SurfaceGui's TextLabel.
         - For groups with duplicates (>=2 blocks), it teleports the player near each block, orients the 
           player toward the block, and reliably fires the "TakeBlock" event.

      3. Auto Buy Upgrades:
         - Provides three independent toggle checkboxes:
             • "Spawnrate" — When enabled, sends the "Cooldown" upgrade request every second.
             • "Max Blocks" — When enabled, sends the "MaxBlocks" upgrade request every second.
             • "Spawn Tier" — When enabled, sends the "SpawnTier" upgrade request every second.
         - Each upgrade is purchased individually as soon as its toggle is enabled.

    All actions run concurrently until toggled off.

    Place this LocalScript in StarterPlayerScripts.
--]]

